The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for recognizing and enumerating bicliques in graphs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the arboricity of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions solving biclique problems, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
